rComments: Take GNG1103 with another professor if possible.

though his courses are tough with lots of home work, they are very beneficial and he's an amazing lecturer. ignore the lazy students complaining about his courses because they are too busy watching game of thrones and playing league of legends. no pain no gain !

Prof Knox had a good sense of humor and cared about our wellbeing. He incorporated "wellness breaks" into our lectures for us to stand and chitchat which was nice. Only thing is sometimes he'd be too aggressive in asking us to turn our cameras on- he wouldn't take no for an answer but didn't force it. Other than that, he was informative and caring.

Prof. Knox is by far the best professor I had last semester. Although his class had a lot of homework, and the subject was not too interesting, Knox made sure to make online lectures engaging and entertaining. You can tell that he truly cares about his students, and is always looking for feedback to improve his teaching and the course in general.

The work load in this course is way too heavy and the grading on the written portion of the quizzes and the exam was extremely tough. I spoke to some of my peers who felt like they did everything that was covered in the lectures on the final exam and still received a low grade. He marks as though nobody has any other courses to worry about.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Tough grader', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: Prof Knox is the best prof that I have had so far. He actually listens to the feedback you give him and he works hard to make sure the course is fair. While for our section, we had probably the worst client ever, Knox worked really hard on making sure that we had everything we could need to succeed. I hope to have him in the future for my classes.

Knox is a great professor, but the workload for this course is quite massive. However, most of the project work is pretty simple, there's just a lot of it, along with weekly labs and midterms. Put in the work and you will be just fine.

Knox puts in clear effort to make lectures more enjoyable, and wont hesitate to help outside of class. The class itself was horrible. Poorly organized and too much work. Only one lab was related to the project.

The amount of work for this class is just absurd along with the TAs expectation with the weekly assignments. The course itself is fine but it shouldn't be filled up with so many assignments, labs, quizzes.

Signing up for his class was a big mistake. He gives more work than every other teacher combined. He gives us quizzes with 5 questions and expects us to finish in 6 mins. For these quizzes we need to read a case study and memorize the whole thing before class even starts. He gave us a lab before our first lecture. Every week expect a lab, quiz & HW
People are giving him high ratings for how they like him as a person, not how he is as a prof. Don't be fooled.
So much work for such a pointless class. Lectures are not very useful and can be skipped. Get a good group for the project or you're screwed.

Knox is a pretty nice guy, if you talk to him before class or during his wellness breaks, he's pretty cool, but he expects a lot from his students. He teaches what you need to know to finish group projects but there's still a whole lot you have to teach yourself so just beware of that.

He's actually a really nice guy. Reach out to him, he always offers a helping hand. Aim for 110% on the group project and deliverables, they well literally carry your mark in GNG 1103. Pay attention to the multiple choice as a few are quite tricky. The content of this class is super boring but he tries to make it fun every once in a while.

Don't get me wrong, he's a nice & fun guy. But his quiz and exam marking and feedback is extremely inconsistent from one person to another. Aim for A+'s on all the deliverables and group project in this class to carry your grade. The quizzes are kind of fair but don't be surprised if you end up with an A+ on the first one and an F on the next.
So much pointless work for what should be an easy class.

Professor Knox lectures are fun and engaging but it is not enough to cover for your quizzes or exams. He is always ready to help or answer any questions you have so make that effort. The workload for this course is heavy and very hands-on. I like the group projects(shoutout to my team) but not so much of the deliverables.
teacherRatingTags: ['Group projects', 'Lots of homework', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: Really awesome prof. Good presenter really cares about feedback. Seems determined to truly TEACH, and not just speak to the students. If you can take a course with him, I highly suggest it.

Hardest prof/class of first year. His lectures were genuinely interesting, and I learned so much from him, but his workload/expectations are insane. Had to work super hard to meet his expectations. There's a trade off with him, he's fun but you have to work really hard.

Knox was great. His lectures were awesome and he is hilarious. He really seems to be there to teach not just research. He also has experience in the professional field. He did assign a lot of group work and there are a lot of project deliverables but it wasn't particularly hard. Some labs seemed tedious. 10/10 would take anything he teaches.

So many useless deliverables. I seriously doubt what he is trying to prove is it engineering design or technical report writing? The feedback he gives is trash always criticizes non-important things. Please do yourself a favor. DO NOT TAKE THIS COURSE!!!
Lots of work
Great prof, good at explaining, just not in French. Needs to practice more, which is why I appreciate his efforts.

I dont get why his rating is that low. He's an awesome prof. I saw people saying that he's a harsh marker; the only thing he marks is the design question on midterm and final! TA's mark the rest (labs, assignments, quizzes, deliverables). The class is a decent workload, but if you are wiling to put in 3-4 hours a week, youll get an easy B+ or more.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Amazing lectures ', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Fantastic Prof who really cared about being fair to his students. His style took some time to get used to but after some classes I really started enjoying the course. He asked almost every one if they thought his exams were fair and was always seeking out feedback. Because he was working to be a better teacher I had a lot of respect for him.
Has a very high opinion of himself

Had this prof for design. He's a really good person. Can come off as loud, or talkative or quick to judge, but he recognizes and accepts that he is. He does care for students. Midterms and finals usually have a lot of writing. Be really careful about multiple choice/true-false/multiple answer type questions, they can be tricky.
Too much work
Run for the hills!
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Tough grader']

rComments: An amazing prof. His passion and authentic enthusiasm make him a joy to be around, and a great person to learn from. Going to his lectures is a must, but you won't even mind the slightest.

Best professor I've had so far in my undergraduate career! David is a wonderful prof. You can tell that he truly cares about his students. He is patient, caring and will take the time to clarify any assignment or concept for you. He made class enjoyable and allowed you to really get out of your comfort zone!
He's the best professor I've had and always makes lectures fun to go to but the courses that he teaches have a lot of work and are disorganized
Do not take this course

The critical comments with effort and marking here are more than valid Though it takes some to appreciate future applicable skills contained in his assigned work. His lectures are hilarious, he's passionate and experienced, and great guy to talk to. Also very keen on getting course feedback. Since this was the 1st GNG1103 ever it's very impressive
Gives a ton of work
Professor Knox is a great professor who is clearly very passionate about the course. He's really committed to his students. The course has A LOT of work though
Nice enough dude, but talks about himself a lot
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Denis Waitley once said "The results you achieve will be in direct proportion to the effort you apply." It is obvious Waitley has never taken Knox's engineering design class. Zero correlation between work put in and marks obtained in this course. Knox's weekly deliverances  require several hours of work per week and are marked extremely harshly.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Accessible outside class', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: Knox is a great guy, but don't take his classes expecting them to be bird courses.

Pros:  David knox is an excellent professor who made GNG2101 a very fun course. He would make us laugh a lot, he is understanding and is willing to talk anytime/anywhere. He is a very smart and witty person. Cons: GNG2101 had A LOT of assignments/project work... He is a Self righteous pr*ck who thinks he is never wrong.

I have to say, that David Knox is probably my favourite Professor I have had thus far. He is really fun and engaging and it makes the whole class a blast. The class itself was very entertaining and really compelling, would highly recommend the class and the Professor to anyone.
